<p align=justify><font size="3" face="Arial">Later, Philips released other 
Tele-Spiel models. They no longer used the basic CMOS technology, but used 
dedicated game chips made by General Instruments. The artwork of some of their 
boxes (ES 2203 for example) was really nice.</font></p>

